        <section xml:id="Section_2_3">
        <title>Section 2.3</title>
        

<subsection xml:id="Question_2_3_2">
    <title> Problem 2</title>
    <ol marker="(a)">  
        <li>
            <p>
                If <m>a|b</m>, there exists <m>s</m> such that <m>as=b</m>. Then <m>asc=bc=a(sc)=bc</m> so <m>a|bc</m>.
            </p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <p>
                If <m>a|b</m> and <m>a|c</m> then there exist integers <m>s,t</m> such that <m>as=b</m> and <m>at=c</m>. Multiply these two equations: <m>a^2st=a^2(st)=bc</m>, so <m>a^2|bc</m>.
            </p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <p>
                If <m>a|b</m> then <m>as=b</m> for some integer <m>s</m>. Then <m>asc=ac(s)=bc</m> so <m>ac|bc</m>. Conversely, if <m>ac|bc</m> then <m>act=bc</m> for some integer <m>t</m>. Divide by <m>c</m> to obtain <m>at=b</m>, so <m>a|b</m>.
            </p>
        </li>

        <li>
            <p>
                similar
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</subsection>        

